 potential for social conflict, Kay concludes, the works of novelists and philosophers helped make England the prototype of the settled state, the country that did not have a modern revolution.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Aug 2019) 0aEnglish fictiony18th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aPolitical fiction, EnglishxHistory and criticism. 0aPolitical sciencezGreat BritainxPhilosophyxHistoryy18th century. 0aPolitics and literaturezGreat BritainxHistoryy18th century. 4aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501745928423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501745928.jpg  aPDA5EBK  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA14ALL  aPDA1ALL